<item>
            <title>[LU-11902] Remove obsolete lustre-utils files and entries for DEB packages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11902</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;DEB packages can be build for server or client, where naming&lt;br/&gt;
convention for server is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lustre-server-modules-*&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lustre-server-utils-*&lt;br/&gt;
and for client:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lustre-client-modules-*&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lustre-client-utils-*&lt;br/&gt;
Previously the util package was named lustre-utils which&lt;br/&gt;
is now obsolete due to the client and server separation&lt;br/&gt;
and thus can be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Debian GNU/Linux 9.7 (stretch)&lt;br/&gt;
4.9.0-8-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.9.130-2 (2018-10-27) x86_64 GNU/Linux</environment>
